Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; white slip. Rectangular stamp with torch symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Sokrates
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0616)
